---

## Overview

This guide explains how to set up and run your JARVIS Personal Assistant using Python.
Your project already contains the code â€” this document only covers environment setup, dependency installation, and how to launch agent.py from the console.

---

## Prerequisites

Before starting, make sure:

* Python 3.10 or higher is installed
* Python is added to PATH
* Your project folder contains:

* agent.py
* requirements.txt

To verify Python:

##python --version

## Step 1 â€” Create Virtual Environment (.venv)

### Windows

python -m venv .venv


### Linux / Mac


python3 -m venv .venv


This creates a .venv directory.

---

## Step 2 â€” Activate Virtual Environment

### Windows


.venv\Scripts\activate


### Linux / Mac


source .venv/bin/activate


After activation, you should see:


(.venv)


This confirms the environment is active.

---

## Step 3 â€” Install Dependencies

Install all required packages:


pip install -r requirements.txt


If pip needs upgrade:


pip install --upgrade pip


Then run again:


pip install -r requirements.txt


Wait until installation finishes.

---

## Step 4 â€” Environment Variables (.env)

If your JARVIS uses API keys (OpenAI, Google, Weather, LiveKit, etc):

Create a .env file in the root folder and add your keys there.

Make sure .env is saved before running JARVIS.

---

## Step 5 â€” Run JARVIS

Start the assistant:


python agent.py


You should see console output similar to:


JARVIS Activated


JARVIS is now running.

---

## Daily Usage

Each time you restart your system:

1. Open terminal in project folder
2. Activate environment

Windows:


.venv\Scripts\activate


Linux / Mac:


source .venv/bin/activate


3. Run JARVIS:


python agent.py


---

## Stop JARVIS

Press:


CTRL + C


---

## Common Issues

### Module not found

Reinstall dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt

---

### Python not recognized

Reinstall Python and enable â€œAdd to PATHâ€.

---

### Permission errors (Windows)

Run Command Prompt as Administrator.

---

## Notes

* Always activate .venv before running
* Keep agent.py in root folder
* Do not delete .venv
* Update requirements.txt when adding new libraries

## Run assistant

* Python agent.py console

---

## Future Enhancements (Optional)

Later you can extend JARVIS with:

* Auto-start on boot
* EXE build
