# ğŸ¤– JARVIS Personal Assistant â€“ Setup Guid brain.py


# ğŸ™ï¸ LiveKit Voice Setup (JARVIS)

This section explains how to install LiveKit, connect your API inside brain.py, and resolve common *live noise cancellation errors*.

---

## âœ… Prerequisites

Make sure:

* Your .venv is activated
* agent.py already runs
* You have LiveKit credentials:

From LiveKit Dashboard:

* LIVEKIT_URL
* LIVEKIT_API_KEY
* LIVEKIT_API_SECRET

---

## ğŸ“¦ Step 1 â€” Install LiveKit Packages

With .venv active, run:


pip install livekit
pip install livekit-agents
pip install livekit-plugins-google
pip install livekit-plugins-noise-cancellation
pip install python-dotenv


Recommended extra audio deps:


pip install sounddevice pyaudio numpy


If pyaudio fails on Windows:


pip install pipwin
pipwin install pyaudio


Then verify:


pip list | findstr livekit


You should see:

* livekit
* livekit-agents
* livekit-plugins-google
* livekit-plugins-noise-cancellation

---

## ğŸ” Step 2 â€” Add LiveKit API Keys

Create or open .env in project root:

Put your credentials there:

* LIVEKIT_URL
* LIVEKIT_API_KEY
* LIVEKIT_API_SECRET

Save file.

Your brain.py should load these using dotenv and initialize LiveKit from there.

(Important: never hardcode keys directly in GitHub.)

---

## ğŸ§  Step 3 â€” brain.py (Voice Brain)

Inside brain.py:

* Load .env
* Initialize LiveKit client
* Create voice agent
* Import all your tools (file, window, keyboard, memory)
* Attach noise cancellation plugin

Conceptually:

brain.py =

Voice Input â†’ LiveKit â†’ Noise Cancellation â†’ JARVIS Tools â†’ Response

Make sure:

âœ” brain.py imports your skill files
âœ” No circular imports

If error appears, first confirm all plugins are installed (Step 1).

---

## ğŸ”Š Step 4 â€” Live Noise Cancellation Error (Common Fix)

If you see errors like:

* noise_cancellation not found
* module not installed
* audio stream failed

Do this:

### 1. Reinstall plugin


pip uninstall livekit-plugins-noise-cancellation -y
pip install livekit-plugins-noise-cancellation


---

### 2. Install audio backend


pip install sounddevice pyaudio


Windows users (if pyaudio fails):


pip install pipwin
pipwin install pyaudio


---

### 3. Restart terminal

Close terminal completely.

Reopen:

Activate env:


.venv\Scripts\activate


Run again:


python brain.py console


---

## ğŸ” Step 5 â€” Import All Tools into brain.py

If JARVIS tools are not working with voice:

Make sure brain.py imports:

* file tools
* window control
* keyboard/mouse
* memory system

Then agent.py should only start brain.

Architecture:

agent.py â†’ brain.py â†’ tools

This avoids confusion.

---

## â–¶ï¸ Final Run

Always run from root:


python brain.py console


If voice works:

Youâ€™ll see mic activation + LiveKit connection.

---

## ğŸ›‘ If Still Error

Check one by one:


pip show livekit
pip show livekit-agents
pip show livekit-plugins-noise-cancellation


If missing â†’ reinstall.

Also confirm:

* Microphone permissions allowed
* No other app using mic
* .env loaded correctly

---

## âœ… Summary

1 Activate .venv
2 Install LiveKit + plugins
3 Add API keys to .env
4 Load keys in brain.py
5 Import all tools in brain.py
6 Run python agent.py

Thatâ€™s it.

